title: Watch an amazing 17-metre dive into the deepest pool on a cruise ship
text:
Watch an amazing 17-metre dive into the deepest pool on a cruise ship Last updated 13:35, February 6 2017 Sydney Brown/INSTAGRAM 
Cesilie Carlton prepares for one heck of a dive on the Harmony of the Seas cruise ship. 
Diving from a 17-metre high platform is scary enough - now imagine that platform is on a moving cruise ship. 
It's clearly no problem for American high diver Cesilie Carlton. Impressive footage shot aboard the Harmony of the Seas cruise ship, where Carlton is a high-dive performer, shows the 35-year-old diving off the platform and performing several somersaults before plunging into the pool below. 
The video was shot and shared on Instagram by fellow diver, Sydney Brown, and has racked up more than 200,000 views since it was posted last week, reports the Daily Mail . A video posted by Sydney Brown (@sydneybrown_xo) on Jan 29, 2017 at 8:47am PST
